    ## Structure & Sectioning
    - [`<main>`][1] to indicate the "real" content
    - [`<header>`][2] for introducting sections
    - [`<footer>`][3] for wrapping up sections
    - [`<article>`][4] for stand alone units of content
    - [`<section>`][5] for grouping of articles
    - [`<aside>`][6] for tangents and sidetracks
    - [`<nav>`][7] for collecting links

    [1]: http://html5doctor.com/the-main-element/
    [2]: http://html5doctor.com/the-header-element/
    [3]: http://html5doctor.com/the-footer-element-update/
    [4]: http://html5doctor.com/the-article-element/
    [5]: http://html5doctor.com/the-section-element/
    [6]: http://html5doctor.com/aside-revisited/
    [7]: http://html5doctor.com/nav-element/

